<heading id="D0D61E62FF83D938BEA32C69FD56863F" box="[136,740,1562,1589]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF83D938BEA32C69FD9F863F" authority="L. A. Cardenas" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,557,1562,1589]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF83D938BEA32C69FECD863E" bold="true" box="[136,383,1562,1589]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Miconia chemillensis</emphasis>
L. A. Cárdenas
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B955751CFF83D938BC1E2C68FD38863F" box="[565,650,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A266C867FF83D938BC1E2C68FD38863F" box="[565,650,1563,1588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131AB58BFF83D938BCB32C69FD6E863F" box="[664,732,1562,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,190,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[151,1435,190,1780]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Miconia chemillensis. A. Flowering branch. B. Inflorescence detail.C. Flower at anthesis. D. Antepetalous stamen, side view. E. Antesepalous stamen in side (L) and ventral view (R) (Cardenas 823, NY)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147233/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EA90EFF83D938BEA32C15FBC886CF" blockId="3.[136,1452,1638,1804]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Shrub or treelet, young stems terete, glabrous, on the blade surface mostly glabrous but with minute glandular trichomes, glomerulate panicle, flowers sessile, 5-merous, stamens dimorphic, antesepalous stamen filaments with an inflection towards the apex and connective with two minute ventral appendages, antepetalous lacking basal connective appendages.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
