<paragraph id="8B9EA90EFF85D93EBE962801FE4782DE" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBE962801FE408287" bold="true" box="[189,498,626,652]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Habitat and Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<materialsCitation id="3B49A353FF85D93EBC3D2801FE4382DE" country="Peru" county="San Daniel area" elevation="2171" location="Endemic" municipality="Yanachaga Chemillen National Park" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" specimenCount="1">
<location id="8EFEFFD5FF85D93EBC3D2801FDC88287" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03881818FF83D93EBEA32C69FAB985E7:8EFEFFD5FF85D93EBC3D2801FDC88287" box="[534,634,626,652]" country="Peru" county="San Daniel area" municipality="Yanachaga Chemillen National Park" name="Endemic" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Endemic</location>
to the central forests of 
<collectingCountry id="F336E99EFF85D93EBD802800FC6C8286" box="[939,990,627,653]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Peru</collectingCountry>
in 
<location id="8EFEFFD5FF85D93EBA262801FB028287" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03881818FF83D93EBEA32C69FAB985E7:8EFEFFD5FF85D93EBA262801FB028287" box="[1037,1200,626,652]" country="Peru" county="San Daniel area" municipality="Yanachaga Chemillen National Park" name="Huancabamba" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Huancabamba</location>
, Oxapampa. 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBB652800FEA082BB" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBB652800FEA082BB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Miconia chemillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="549A17ACFF85D93EBC0B28E4FDE282BA" box="[544,592,663,689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">type</typeStatus>
and has been collected in the border the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BFA3374FF85D93EBA3B28E5FA1582BB" box="[1040,1447,662,688]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Yanachaga Chemillén National Park</collectingMunicipality>
, in the 
<collectingCounty id="62FFD182FF85D93EBEE528C9FE3282DE" box="[206,384,698,725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">San Daniel area</collectingCounty>
(
<quantity id="4CD904EBFF85D93EBFA528C9FE5B82DE" box="[398,489,698,725]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.171" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" unit="m" value="2171.0">
<elevation id="000C4E3DFF85D93EBFA528C9FE5B82DE" box="[398,489,698,725]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.171" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" unit="m" value="2171.0">2171 m</elevation>
</quantity>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33BFA85FF85D93EBE9628ADFDCA83DB" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9EA90EFF85D93EBE9628ADFB1F8317" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBE9628ADFE8C82F3" bold="true" box="[189,318,734,760]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Etymology</emphasis>
:—This new species is named after the Yanachaga Chemillén National Park where is found. Chemillén is a Yanesha word that means “burnt” and it refers to the aspect of the mountains of the region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EA90EFF85D93EBEA32955FDCA83DB" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBEA32955FECB834B" bold="true" box="[136,377,806,832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Conservation Status</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBFB72954FD3B834B" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" box="[412,649,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBFB72954FD3B834B" box="[412,649,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Miconia chemillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known only from one population a at the border of the Yanachaga Chemillen National Park, in an area that is highly degraded and under logging pressure. Based on the paucity of collections it should be considered Data Deficient (DD), following the IUCN criteria (2001) as implemented by the IUCN guidelines (2011). However, based on its limited distribution and endangered habitat, we recommend that this species is considered Critically Endangered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33BFA85FF85D93EBE9629A9FAB985E7" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9EA90EFF85D93EBE9629A9FE91851E" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBE9629A9FE8983FF" bold="true" box="[189,315,986,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Discussion</emphasis>
:—The anthers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBC2A29A8FD5F83FF" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" box="[513,749,986,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBC2A29A8FD5F83FF" box="[513,749,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Miconia chemillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a slender but prolonged connective with apically widening thecae that open by broad pores. These characteristics place this new species in the traditional definition of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBB65298CFC7D8437" authority="(Richard ex de Candolle 1828: 180) Triana ex Hook." authorityName="Triana ex Hook." baseAuthorityName="Richard ex de Candolle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="180" baseAuthorityYear="1828" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Hypoxanthus">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBB65298CFA198413" box="[1358,1451,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Miconia</emphasis>
section 
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBEF42E51FEC18437" box="[223,371,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Hypoxanthus</emphasis>
(Richard ex 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF85D93EBC2E2E51FCB78437" author="de Candolle, A. P." box="[517,773,1058,1084]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" refId="ref8429" refString="de Candolle, A. P. (1828) Memoires sur la famille des Melastomacees. Treuttel et Wurtz, Paris, 82 pp." type="book" year="1828">de Candolle 1828: 180</bibRefCitation>
) Triana ex Hook.
</taxonomicName>
f., in Bentham &amp; Hooker (1867: 764), also known as 
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBED42E34FEA4846B" box="[255,278,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M</emphasis>
. section 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBFAB2E35FC50846B" authority="(Crueger 1847: 111) Triana ex Hook." authorityName="Hook." baseAuthorityName="Crueger" baseAuthorityPageNumber="111" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[384,994,1094,1121]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Glossocentrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBFAB2E35FD98846B" box="[384,554,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Glossocentrum</emphasis>
(Crueger 1847: 111) Triana ex Hook.
</taxonomicName>
f. in Bentham &amp; Hook (1867: 763); see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF85D93EBEA32E19FED6848F" author="Goldenberg, R." box="[136,356,1130,1156]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" refId="ref8628" refString="Goldenberg, R. (2000) O Genero Miconia Ruiz &amp; Pav. (Melastomataceae): I. Listagens analiticas, II. Revisao Taxonomica da Secao Hypoxanthus (Rich. ex DC.) Hook. F. Ph. D. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Estadual de Campinas, Campinas, 249 pp." type="book" year="2000">Goldenberg (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. The great majority of the species in this group are from Eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F336E99EFF85D93EBA4B2E19FB16848F" box="[1120,1188,1130,1156]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Brazil</collectingCountry>
but eleven species are known from 
<collectingCountry id="F336E99EFF85D93EBF322EFCFEE284A2" box="[281,336,1167,1193]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Peru</collectingCountry>
. The members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBC312EFCFCDB84A3" authorityName="Triana ex Hook." baseAuthorityName="Richard ex de Candolle" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[538,873,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Hypoxanthus">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBC312EFCFDC584A3" box="[538,631,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Miconia</emphasis>
section 
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBCFE2EFDFCDB84A3" box="[725,873,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Hypoxanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F336E99EFF85D93EBDA62EFCFC7284A2" box="[909,960,1167,1193]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Peru</collectingCountry>
are mostly found below 
<quantity id="4CD904EBFF85D93EBAF22EFDFA9384A2" box="[1241,1313,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
elevation in Amazonian forests, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBF802EC0FDE884C7" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" box="[427,602,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBF802EC0FDE884C7" box="[427,602,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. chemillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in cloud forests ca. 
<quantity id="4CD904EBFF85D93EBDFF2EC1FB9A84C6" box="[980,1064,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" unit="m" value="2500.0">2500 m</quantity>
elevation. Molecular phylogenetic work is necessary to ascertain whether this species is indeed closely related to the Brazilian species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBAD32EA4FEAE851F" authorityName="Triana ex Hook." baseAuthorityName="Richard ex de Candolle" baseAuthorityYear="1828" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Hypoxanthus">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBAD32EA4FAE784FB" box="[1272,1365,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Miconia</emphasis>
section 
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBEA32E89FEAE851F" box="[136,284,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Hypoxanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EA90EFF85D93EBE962F6DFAB985E7" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">
The flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBF4D2F6CFDA78533" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" box="[358,533,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBF4D2F6CFDA78533" box="[358,533,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. chemillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBD112F6CFB798532" authority="Gleason (1936: 535)" authorityName="Gleason" authorityPageNumber="535" authorityYear="1936" box="[826,1227,1310,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semisterilis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBD112F6CFC6D8533" box="[826,991,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. semisterilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF85D93EBDCF2F6DFB798532" author="Gleason, H. A." box="[996,1227,1310,1337]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" pagination="533 - 537" refId="ref8591" refString="Gleason, H. A. (1936) Seven American Melastomes. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 63: 533 - 537. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 2480934" type="journal article" year="1936">Gleason (1936: 535)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, especially in calyx, style and anther shape. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBFD52F30FD1F8557" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" box="[510,685,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBFD52F30FD1F8557" box="[510,685,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. chemillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dimorphic anthers (as opposed to isomorphic in 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBADC2F30FA298557" authorityName="Gleason" authorityYear="1936" box="[1271,1435,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semisterilis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBADC2F30FA298557" box="[1271,1435,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. semisterilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 5-merous flowers (vs. 4-merous). Additionally, the inflorescence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBD952F14FBDD858B" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" box="[958,1135,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBD952F14FBDD858B" box="[958,1135,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. chemillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is glomerulate (flowers not clustered in 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBF3D2FF8FE0C85AF" authorityName="Gleason" authorityYear="1936" box="[278,446,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semisterilis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBF3D2FF8FE0C85AF" box="[278,446,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. semisterilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the leaves are glabrous abaxially (vs. densely stellate-pubescent). Vegetatively 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBBA62FF8FEA085C3" authorityName="L. A. Cardenas" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chemillensis">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBBA62FF8FEA085C3" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. chemillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBFBE2FDCFD4085C3" authority="Gleason (1931: 240)" authorityName="Gleason" authorityPageNumber="240" authorityYear="1931" box="[405,754,1454,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBFBE2FDCFE4F85C3" box="[405,509,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. klugii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF85D93EBC2D2FDDFD4085C3" author="Gleason, H. A." box="[518,754,1454,1480]" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" pagination="215 - 262" refId="ref8518" refString="Gleason, H. A. (1931) Studies on the flora of northern South America-XV. Recent collections of Melastomataceae from Peru and Amazonian Brazil. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 58: 215 - 262. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 2480704" type="journal article" year="1931">Gleason (1931: 240)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, also from 
<collectingCountry id="F336E99EFF85D93EBD532FDCFC1C85C2" box="[888,942,1455,1481]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">Peru</collectingCountry>
, but differs in leaf pubescence (glabrous vs. densely stellate) and the anthers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF85D93EBC382FA0FDCA85E7" authorityName="Gleason" authorityYear="1931" box="[531,632,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF85D93EBC382FA0FDCA85E7" box="[531,632,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="126">M. klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack the connective below the fertile portion of the thecae.
</paragraph>
